JSBSim is an object-oriented, multi-platform, FDM (Flight Dynamics Model). It
is currently the default FDM for the open source, multi-platform, FlightGear
flight simulator. Scroll down for an overview of  JSBSim. JSBSim is currently
being developed by:

Jon Berndt, Texas, U.S.A., Architect & Coordinator
Tony Peden, Washington, U.S.A., Co-Author
David Megginson, Canada, Developer
Erik Hofman, The Netherlands, Developer
David Culp, Illinois, U.S.A., Developer

